Initially the strain energy of the epitaxial film increases with thickness, and beyond the critical thickness some of this energy will be accomodated by the formation of misfit dislocation. In our previous works, we have developed an energy balance model for the step-graded structure to calculate the misfit dislocation density [45, 46]. It has been reported that the misfit strain in the heteroepitaxy starts to relax after hc at each interlayer; the layer will be partially relaxed by MDs. In order to do this, the strain energy of each interlayer and energy accomodated by misfit dislocations have been calcualted. One important term in that calculation was the consideration of residual strain using the nonzero component of elastic constant, after a thickness of h is [46, 47]3εi=εmi-32bciρMDi\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
